{
  "texts": [
    "Predicting academic performance early on is a vital feature within online learning management systems, as it facilitates the timely identification of students who might fail or withdraw.",
    "This paves the way for active intervention strategies or measures to assist these students in bolstering their skills and comprehension.",
    "We bifurcated this task into two parts: early prediction for students at risk of failing by classifying them as Pass or Fail, and early prediction for students at risk of withdrawal by classifying them as Pass or Withdrawn.",
    "Experimental settings were similar except for the duration (weeks 5, 10, 15, and 20) utilized for training and testing from learning logs.Table 5 reports the comparison results between the baseline models and APP-DGNN in early predicting at-risk students regarding accuracy.",
    "It can be seen that APP-DGNN still outperforms the other baseline models in all learning periods, showing a more impressive performance compared to the results in Table 4."
  ]
}